Gauteng premier David Makhura says the ruling party needs professionals to participate in ANC programs to transform the country. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng acting African National Congress (ANC) chair and provincial premier David Makhura has called on professionals and academics to participate in the political heart of the ruling party. Makhura was speaking at an ANC event, where the professionals and academics are in dialogue with President Cyril Ramaphosa. Makhura says the ruling party needs professionals to participate in ANC programs to transform the country. “As we move forward with renewal, we need more amongst the professional structures to participate in the ranks of the ANC. The organisational renewal belongs to them as well.”  (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)